OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEx-mining towns falling    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffurther behind - charity   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Former coal-mining areas are falling   
OL,6, further behind the rest of Britain     
OL,7, decades on from pit closures, a charity
OL,8, has warned.                            
OL,10,FForty years after the 1984 miners'     
OL,11,Fstrike, the Coalfields Regeneration    
OL,12,FTrust (CRT) said communities had been  
OL,13,F"let down" by a lack of investment     
OL,14,Fsince the loss of an industry which    
OL,15,Femployed more than 220,000 people.     
OL,18,FThe government said it had committed   
OL,19,F#15bn to improve the lives of          
OL,20,F"everyone, everywhere in the UK"       
OL,21,Fthrough levelling-up projects.         
